  "text": "We conclude this section by noting that the target characteristics reflected in the vector Â contain many parameters, some of which may be more important than others for a given task. For example, if the only goal is to detect and locate a buried conducting target, then the spatial position of the target ðx; y; zÞ should be given more importance than the remaining target parameters. In such situations, the significance of important parameters in Â should be reflected in the cost function. In the UXO-sensing problem considered in Section 4, it is insufficient to simply detect and locate the target: The goal is to distinguish actual UXO from non-UXO conducting clutter. It has been demonstrated that all target parameters in the vector Â are important for this classification task [CITATION_1] . Therefore, in the above analysis, we have chosen the new sensor parameters p p Nþ1 to minimize the overall \"error bars\" in the model parameters, considering the importance of all parameters in Â.",
